ABOUT THIS RESEARCH 

You are being asked to participate in a research study. Scientists do research to answer questions and learn new information. Some research might help change or improve the way we do things in the future. This consent information will tell you more about the study to help you decide whether you want to participate. Please read this information before agreeing to be in the study.
WHO CAN PARTICIPATE
American citizens age 18 or older.

 

TAKING PART IN THIS STUDY IS VOLUNTARY

Your participation is voluntary; you are free to withdraw your participation from the study at any time. If you do not want to continue, you can simply leave the website. If you do not click on the button at the end of the survey to “Receive you Confirmation Code,” your answers and participation will not be included in the study. You may also choose to skip any questions that you do not wish to answer. However, failure to complete the majority of the questions may result in your MTurk account not being credited for successful completion of the HIT. 

 

WHY IS THIS STUDY BEING DONE?

The purpose of this study is to understand what makes photographs iconic. The answers you provide will be used for a research study testing hypotheses on the power of images being conducted at the University of Notre Dame. 

 

You were selected as a possible participant because you are an American citizen. 

 

The study is being conducted by Terence McDonnell, Department of Sociology, University of Notre Dame. It is funded by the Institute for Scholarship in the Liberal Arts. 

 

HOW MANY PEOPLE WILL TAKE PART?

If you agree to participate, you will be one of thousands of participants taking part in this study.

 

WHAT WILL HAPPEN DURING THE STUDY?

If you agree to be in the study, you will be asked to do the following things:

 

·       You’ll be asked to make choices among images

·       You’ll answer questions about the meaning of the American Presidency

·       You’ll be asked about your basic demographic information and political orientation

 

WHAT ARE THE RISKS OF TAKING PART IN THE STUDY?

No risks or discomforts are anticipated from taking part in this study. If you feel uncomfortable with a question, you can skip that question or withdraw from the study altogether. If you decide to quit before you have finished the questionnaire and received your confirmation code, your answers will not be included in the study. 

 

WHAT ARE THE POTENTIAL BENEFITS OF TAKING PART IN THE STUDY?

We don’t expect you to receive any benefit from taking part in this study, but we hope to learn things that will help scientists in the future.

 

HOW WILL MY INFORMATION BE PROTECTED?

Efforts will be made to keep your personal information confidential. We cannot guarantee absolute confidentiality.  Your personal information may be disclosed if required by law. No information which could identify you will be shared in publications about this study and databases in which results may be stored.

 

Organizations that may inspect and/or copy your research records for quality assurance and data analysis include groups such as the study investigator and his/her research associates, the University of Notre Dame Institutional Review Board or its designees, and (as allowed by law) state or federal agencies, especially the Office for Human Research Protections (OHRP), who may need to access the research records.

 

Your Mechanical Turk Worker ID will be used to distribute payment to you but will not be stored with the research data we collect from you. Please be aware that your MTurk Worker ID can potentially be linked to information about you on your Amazon public profile page, depending on the settings you have for your Amazon profile. We will not be accessing any personally identifying information about you that you may have put on your Amazon public profile page.

 

WILL I BE PAID FOR PARTICIPATION? 

You will receive $2 for participation in this study. Payments will occur through Amazon Mechanical Turk upon completion of the Human Intelligence Task (HIT). MTurk does not allow for prorated compensation. In the event of an incomplete HIT you will not receive any compensation. A few early questions will assess whether you are qualified to participate in the survey. This study contains a number of checks to make sure that participants are finishing the tasks honestly and completely. As long as you read the instructions and complete the tasks, your HIT will be approved. If you fail these checks, your HIT will be rejected and you will not receive any compensation.

 

WHO SHOULD I CALL WITH QUESTIONS OR PROBLEMS?

If you have concerns or questions about this study, please contact Dr. Terence McDonnell at (574) 631-7599 or send an email to temndsociology@gmail.com. This study has been reviewed and approved by The University’s Institutional Review Board and the study number is 16-10-3378.

 

For questions about your rights or any dissatisfaction with any part of this study, you can contact, anonymously if you wish, the Notre Dame Research Compliance Office, at 574-631-1461 or by email at compliance@nd.edu .

 

PARTICIPANT’S CONSENT

 

In consideration of all of the above, I give my consent to participate in this research study. By proceeding,  I confirm that I am an American citizen, at least 18 years old, and I agree to take part in this study.
